        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 12:18AM MDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 1217 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking the outflow from strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 9 miles north of Thunder
Hawk to near Chance. Movement was east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bullhead, Mcintosh, Isabel, Morristown, Firesteel, Watauga, Black
Horse, Walker, Thunder Hawk, Keldron, Shambo Ranch, Klein Ranch, and
southern Standing Rock Nation.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
